\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Champion metric (higher is better) versus experiment index for coordinated teams (solid) and the single-thread baseline (dashed) under a matched experiment budget. Coordinated teams partition the same sequential budget as the baseline rather than adding parallel compute, so this is a robustness/efficiency comparison, not a speedup. Produced by \breaktt {run\_search\_comparison.py}.}}{6}{figure.caption.2}\protected@file@percent }
